<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<%- include('../partials/head') %>
<body class="page page--<%= pageClass %>">
<%- include('../partials/header') %>
<main id="main" class="main main--product">

  <section class="scene scene--hero scene--ledger">
    <div class="scene__glow scene__glow--ledger" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="container scene__inner">
      <p class="eyebrow reveal" data-reveal>Ledger</p>
      <h1 class="scene__title reveal" data-reveal><%= PRODUCTS.ledger.headline %></h1>
      <p class="scene__lead reveal" data-reveal><%= PRODUCTS.ledger.subhead %></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="scene scene--split">
    <div class="container scene__split">
      <div class="scene__visual reveal" data-reveal>
        <div class="scene__panel scene__panel--ledger" aria-hidden="true">
          <span class="scene__lines"></span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="scene__copy reveal" data-reveal>
        <h2 class="scene__h">Vault first—then documents, filled exactly</h2>
        <p>Ledger is a local-first encrypted identity vault and deterministic document prefilling system. It is not a “documents tab” inside another app; it is built for sensitive identity data and precise execution.</p>
        <p>Stored material can include identity fields (including sensitive items such as SSN where you choose to store them), address history, employment history, relationships, documents, and profiles for <strong>up to two people</strong>—for example, you and a spouse—structured and encrypted on your machine.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="scene scene--feature">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <h2 class="scene__h scene__h--center reveal" data-reveal>People and references</h2>
      <p class="scene__center reveal" data-reveal>Ledger includes a People system for those you have known: relationship type, company, role, relevance, and when you met them.</p>
      <p class="scene__center reveal" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1">Duration is computed from <strong>local system time</strong>—so “how long you have known someone” updates naturally; it is never a static string you have to fix by hand.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="scene scene--split scene--reverse">
    <div class="container scene__split">
      <div class="scene__copy reveal" data-reveal>
        <h2 class="scene__h">Deterministic filling—never invented answers</h2>
        <p>Ledger maps document fields to stored data and fills only exact known values. If a value is missing, Ledger does not guess or infer.</p>
        <p><strong><%= SITE.steward.name %></strong> assists with parsing documents, mapping fields, and guiding workflows. It does <em>not</em> generate answers for you. The bar is correctness and auditability, not autocomplete theater.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="scene__visual reveal" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1">
        <div class="scene__panel scene__panel--grid" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="scene scene--ecosystem">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="scene__h reveal" data-reveal>Alongside CFO and Eden</h2>
      <p class="scene__lead reveal" data-reveal><strong>CFO</strong> handles financial operating logic. <strong>Eden</strong> handles research ingestion and evaluation. Ledger handles identity, references, and document execution—all three premium, local-first, and connected through Steward without collapsing into one generic tool.</p>
      <div class="ecosystem-links reveal" data-reveal>
        <a href="product-cfo.html" class="ecosystem-links__a">CFO</a>
        <a href="product-eden.html" class="ecosystem-links__a">Eden</a>
        <a href="compare.html" class="ecosystem-links__a">Compare all</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%- include('../partials/availability-status') %>

</main>
<%- include('../partials/footer') %>
<%- include('../partials/mobile-nav') %>
<script type="module" src="/src/main.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
